text: Washtenaw County () is a county located in the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2020 census, the population was 372,258. The county seat is Ann Arbor. The county is home to the University of Michigan, Eastern Michigan University, Washtenaw Community College, and Concordia University Ann Arbor. ==References== Category:1820s establishments in Michigan Territory Category:1826 establishments in the United States Category:Michigan counties
